Implement Matrices

Categorical Cross Entropy

\[\begin{equation} L_{\mathrm{CE}}=-\sum_{i=1}^{n} t_{i} \log \left(p_{i}\right), \text { for } \mathrm{n} \text { classes } \end{equation}\]

Where \(t_i\) the true label and \(p_i\) is the softmax probability for the \(i^{th}\) class

More details about Categorical Cross Entropy

eplison_loss <- 1e-7 # to avoid issue raise by log(0):-Inf
cat_cross_entropy <- function(y_true, y_pred){
  loss <- rowMeans(y_true * log(y_pred + eplison_loss))
  sum(-loss)
}

Binary Cross-Entropy Loss

\[\begin{equation} L=-\frac{1}{N}\left[\sum_{j=1}^{N}\left[t_{j} \log \left(p_{j}\right)+\left(1-t_{j}\right) \log \left(1-p_{j}\right)\right]\right] \end{equation}\]

Where \(t_i\) the true label and \(p_i\) is the sigmoid probability for the \(i^{th}\) class

bin_cross_entropy <- function(y_true, y_pred){
  loss  <- y_true * log(y_pred)  + (1 - y_true) * log(1-y_pred + eplison_loss)  
  sum(-loss)
}

Mean squared error

\[\begin{equation} \mathrm{MSE}=\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n}\left(Y_{i}-\hat{Y}_{i}\right)^{2} \end{equation}\]

mean_square_error <- function(y_true, y_pred){
    mean((y_true - y_pred)^2)
}

Imputing Data with MICE

miss_data <- add_missingness(data, prop = 0.1)
imp <-  mice(miss_data, print=F)
meth <- imp$meth
meth[c('sex','reg')] <- "rf"
meth[c('age','hgt','wgt')] <- 'norm'

imp <- mice(miss_data, m=10, meth = meth, print=F)
imp100  <-  mice.mids(imp, maxit=5, print=F)
plot(imp100)
